Pb2+ standard solution with different concentrations were used to evaluate the detection ability of the established sensing platform. As shown in Fig. 6
                        A, the elevated Pb2+ concentrations from 0.5 pM to 5 nM lead to the ECL emission gradual increased. The calibration curve shown in Fig. 6B exhibited a good relationship (R = 0.9923) between the ECL intensity and the logarithm concentration of Pb2+, and the corresponding linear equation was I = 1634.2 lgc + 984.9, where I is the ECL intensity and c represents the concentration of Pb2+. And the limit of detection (LOD) was estimated to be 0.27 pM at the signal-to-noise ratio of 3 (Yang et al., 2018). The presented method also exhibited a comparable or superior analytical performance, compared with those strategies reported previously (Table 1
                        ).
